Mui Basin residents have urged the government to come up with better methods of mining.Yesterday, they said the open-cast method will force them to relocate. Former Public Works PS and Mwingi Central MP hopeful Gideon Mulyungi yesterday said residents live in fear of being evicted.He accused the Liaison Committee of keeping residents in the dark. Mulyungi said, Residents do not want to leave their ancestral land and go to a strange place. I want to make sure their interests are protected. 